SIMPLE: misery
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Misery
<hw>Mi"ser*y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Miseries</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[OE. <ets>miserie</ets>, L.
<ets>miseria</ets>, fr. <ets>miser</ets> wretched: cf. F.
<ets>mis⟦egrave⟧re</ets>, OF. also, <ets>miserie</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Great unhappiness; extreme pain of body or mind;
wretchedness; distress; woe.</def> <rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Destruction and <qex>misery</qex> are in their ways.</q>
<rj><qau>Rom. iii. 16.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Cause of misery; calamity; misfortune.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>When we our betters see bearing our woes,⟦br⟧
We scarcely think our <qex>miseries</qex> our foes.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Covetousness; niggardliness; avarice.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Wretchedness; torture; agony; torment; anguish;
distress; calamity; misfortune.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Misesteem</ent>⟦br⟧
